        "translation":  "We call the doer of fair deeds, to our assistance day by day.\nCome thou to our libations! The rich One\u0027s rapture giveth kine.\nMay we be acquainted with thine innermost benevolence.\nGo to the wise unconquered One, ask thou of Indra, skilled in song, him who is better than thy friends.\nYe who serve Indra and non else;\nOr whether, Deva of wondrous deeds, all our true people call us blest, Stil. May we dwell in Indra\u0027s care.\nUnto the swift One bring the swift, man-cheering, grace of offering, that to the Friend gives wings and joy.\nThou helpest the warrior in the fray.\nWe strengthen, thee the powerful, Indra, we may win us wealth.\nTo him the mighty stream of wealth, prompt friend of him, to this Indra sing your song."
