        "translation":  "COME, Indra, Protector, mighty in thy strength.\nO Lord of all men, fair of cheek, rejoice thee in the gladdening lauds, present at these water-offerings.\nSongs have outpoured themselves to thee, Indra, the strong, the guardian Lord, and raised themselves unsatisfied.\nSend to us bounty manifold, O Indra, worthy of our wish, for power supreme is only thine.\nO Indra, O most splendid One.\nGive, Indra, wide and lofty fame, wealthy in strength, lasting our life-time.\nGrant us high fame, O Indra, grant riches, those fair fruits of Earth borne home in wains.\nPraising with songs, we call Indra, the Treasure-Lord of wealth.\nTo lofty Indra, dweller by each libation, the pious man sings forth aloud a strengthening hymn."
