        "translation":  "Now Morning with her earliest light shines forth, dear Daughter of the Sky: High, Indra, I extol your praise,\nSons of the Sea, mighty to save discoverers of riches, ye Devas with deep thought who find out wealth.\nYour giant coursers hasten on over the region all in flames, When your car flies with winged steeds.\nHe, liberal, lover of the flood, Lord of the House, the vigilant, Chiefs! with oblations feeds you full.\nYe have regard unto our hymns, NÄsatyas, thinking of our words: Drink boldly of the Soma juice.\nVouchsafe to us, O AÅ›vin Pair, such strength as, with attendant light, may through the darkness carry us.\nCome in the ship of these our hymns to bear you to the hither shore O Indra, harness ye the car.\nThe Heaven\u0027s wide vessel is your own on the flood\u0027s shore your chariot waits Drops, with the hymn, have been prepared.\nKaá¹‡vas, the drops are in the Heaven; the wealth is at the waters\u0027 place: Where will ye manifest your form?\nLight came to lighten up the branch, the Sun appeared as it were gold: And with its tongue shone forth the dark.\nThe path of offering was made to travel to the farther goal: The road of Heaven was manifest.\nThe singer of their praise awaits whatever grace the Indra givepath of offering.\nYe dwellers with VivasvÄn come, auspicious come to our offering.\nO circumambient Indra, Dawn follows the brightness of your way: Approve with beams our solemn rites.\nDrink ye of our libations, grant protection, O ye Indra Twain, with aids which non. May interrupt."
