        "text":  "१० प्रस्कण्वः काण्वः। अश्विनौ। प्रगाथः – विषमा बृहत्यः, समा सतोबृहत्यः।\n\n        अ॒यं वां॒ मधु॑मत्तमः सु॒तः सोम॑ ऋतावृधा ।\n\n        तम॑श्विना पिबतं ति॒रोअ॑ह्न्यं ध॒त्तं रत्ना॑नि दा॒शुषे॑ ॥१॥\n\n        त्रि॒व॒न्धु॒रेण॑ त्रि॒वृता॑ सु॒पेश॑सा॒ रथे॒ना या॑तमश्विना ।\n\n        कण्वा॑सो वां॒ ब्रह्म॑ कृण्वन्त्यध्व॒रे तेषां॒ सु शृ॑णुतं॒ हव॑म् ॥२॥\n\n        अश्वि॑ना॒ मधु॑मत्तमं पा॒तं सोम॑मृतावृधा ।\n\n        अथा॒द्य द॑स्रा॒ वसु॒ बिभ्र॑ता॒ रथे॑ दा॒श्वांस॒मुप॑ गच्छतम् ॥३॥\n\n        त्रि॒ष॒ध॒स्थे ब॒र्हिषि॑ विश्ववेदसा॒ मध्वा॑ य॒ज्ञं मि॑मिक्षतम् ।\n\n        कण्वा॑सो वां सु॒तसो॑मा अ॒भिद्य॑वो यु॒वां ह॑वन्ते अश्विना ॥४॥\n\n        याभि॒: कण्व॑म॒भिष्टि॑भि॒: प्राव॑तं यु॒वम॑श्विना ।\n\n        ताभि॒: ष्व१स्माँ अ॑वतं शुभस्पती पा॒तं सोम॑मृतावृधा ॥५॥\n\n        सु॒दासे॑ दस्रा॒ वसु॒ बिभ्र॑ता॒ रथे॒ पृक्षो॑ वहतमश्विना ।\n\n        र॒यिं स॑मु॒द्रादु॒त वा॑ दि॒वस्पर्य॒स्मे ध॑त्तं पुरु॒स्पृह॑म् ॥६॥\n\n        यन्ना॑सत्या परा॒वति॒ यद्वा॒ स्थो अधि॑ तु॒र्वशे॑ ।\n\n        अतो॒ रथे॑न सु॒वृता॑ न॒ आ ग॑तं सा॒कं सूर्य॑स्य र॒श्मिभि॑: ॥७॥\n\n        अ॒र्वाञ्चा॑ वां॒ सप्त॑योऽध्वर॒श्रियो॒ वह॑न्तु॒ सव॒नेदुप॑ ।\n\n        इषं॑ पृ॒ञ्चन्ता॑ सु॒कृते॑ सु॒दान॑व॒ आ ब॒र्हिः सी॑दतं नरा ॥८॥\n\n        तेन॑ नास॒त्या ग॑तं॒ रथे॑न॒ सूर्य॑त्वचा ।\n\n        येन॒ शश्व॑दू॒हथु॑र्दा॒शुषे॒ वसु॒ मध्व॒: सोम॑स्य पी॒तये॑ ॥९॥\n\n        उ॒क्थेभि॑र॒र्वागव॑से पुरू॒वसू॑ अ॒र्कैश्च॒ नि ह्व॑यामहे ।\n\n        शश्व॒त् कण्वा॑नां॒ सद॑सि प्रि॒ये हि कं॒ सोमं॑ प॒पथु॑रश्विना ॥१०॥",
        "translation":  "AÅšVINS, for you who strengthen Law this sweetest Soma hath been shed.\nDrink this expressed ere yesterday and give riches to him who offers it.\nCome, O ye Indra, mounted on your triple car three-seated, beautiful of form To you at offerings the Kaá¹‡vas send the prayer: graciously listen to their call.\nO Indra, ye who strengthen Law, drink ye this sweetest Soma juice. Borne on your wealth-fraught car come ye this day to him who offers, ye of wondrous deeds.\nOmniscient Indra, on the thrice-heaped grass bedew with the sweet juice the offering. The sons of Kaá¹‡va, striving heavenward, call on you with draughts of Soma juice out-poured.\nO Indra, with those aids wherewith ye guarded Kaá¹‡va carefully, Keep us, O Lords of Splendour: drink the Soma juice, ye strengtheners of holy law.\nO Mighty Ones, ye gave SudÄs abundant food, brought on your treasure-laden car; So now vouchsafe to us the wealth which many crave, either from Heaven or from the sea.\nNÄsatyas, whether ye be far away or close to TurvaÅ›a, Borne on your lightly-rolling chariot come to us, together with the sunbeams come.\nSo let your coursers bring you to our libations here. Bestowing food on him who acts and gives aright, sit, Chiefs, upon the sacred grass.\nCome, O NÄsatyas, on your car decked with a sunbright canopy, Whereon ye ever bring wealth to the worshipper, \u0027s pleasant juice.\nWith lauds and songs of praise we call them down to us, that they, most rich. May assist us; For ye have ever in the Kaá¹‡vas\u0027 well-loved house, O Indra."
