t.\nMay Uá¹£as whose auspicious rays are seen resplendent round about, Grant us great riches, fair in form, of all good things, wealth which light labou. May attain.\nMighty One, whom the á¹šá¹£is of old time invoked for their protection and their help, O Uá¹£as, graciously answer our songs of praise with bounty and with brilliant light.\nUá¹£as, as thou with light to day hast opened the twin doors of Heaven, So grant thou us a dwelling wide and free from foes. O Goddess, give us food with kine.\nBring us to wealth abundant, sent in every shape, to plentiful refreshing food, to all-subduing splendour, Uá¹£as, Mighty One, to strength, thou rich in spoil and wealth."
