        "translation":  "CHASING with light our sin away, O Agni, shine thou wealth on us.\nMay his light chase our sin away.\nFor goodly fields, for pleasant homes, for wealth we offering to thee. May his light chase our sin away.\nBest praiser of all these be he; foremost, our chiefs who offering. May his light chase our sin away.\nSo that thy worshippers and we, thine, Agni, in our son. May live. May his light chase our sin away.\nAs ever-conquering Agni\u0027s beams of splendour go to every side, may his light chase our sin away.\nTo every side thy face is turned, thou art triumphant everywhere. May his light chase our sin away.\nO thou whose face looks every way, bear us past foes as in a ship. May his light chase our sin away.\nAs in a ship, convey thou us for our advantage oâ€™er the flood. May his light chase our sin away."
