.\nFirm is this new-wrought hymn of praise, and meet to be told forth, O Devas. The flowing of the floods is Law, Truth is the Sun\u0027s extended light. Mark this my woe, ye Earth and Heaven.\nWorthy of laud, O Agni, is that kinship which thou hast with Devas. Here seat thee like a man: most wise, bring thou the Devas for offering. Mark this my woe, ye Earth and Heaven.\nHere seated, man-like as a priest shall wisest Agni to the Devas Speed onward our oblations, Deva among the Devas, intelligent. Mark this my woe, ye Earth and Heaven.\nIndra makes the holy prayer. To him who finds the path we pray. He in the heart reveals his thought. Let sacred worship rise anew. Mark this my woe, ye Earth and Heaven.\nThat pathway of the Sun in Heaven, made to be highly glorified, is not to be transgressed, O Devas. O mortals, ye behold it not. Mark this my woe, ye Earth and Heaven.\nTá¹›ta, when buried in the well, calls on the Devas to assist him. That call of his Soma heard and released him from distress. Mark this my woe, ye Earth and Heaven.\nA ruddy wolf beheld me once, as I was faring on my path. He, like a carpenter whose back is aching crouched and slunk away. Mark this my woe, ye Earth and Heaven.\nThrough this our son. May we, allied with Indra, with all our heroes conquer in the battle. This prayer of our. May Indra grant, and Mitra, and Aditi and Sindhu, Earth and Heaven."
